data.chText: 她完全意识到了所涉及的问题。
data.enText: She's very conscious of the problems involved.

data.chText: 他深深感到自己辜负了父母的期望。
data.enText: He became acutely conscious of having failed his parents.

data.chText: 我隐隐约约地觉察到有人在监视我。
data.enText: I was vaguely conscious that I was being watched.

data.chText: 神志清醒的；有知觉的；有意识的
data.enText: able to use your senses and mental powers to understand what is happening

data.chText: 神志并非完全清醒的病人必须时刻有人照料。
data.enText: A patient who is not fully conscious should never be left alone.

data.chText: 我刻意约束自己准时到达那里。
data.enText: I made a conscious effort to get there on time.

data.chText: 他们的健康意识越来越强。
不管是有意还是无意，你已作出了选择。
data.enText: Consciously or unconsciously, you made a choice.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + sci 知道 + ous …的 → 都知道该怎么做 → 自觉的

ex.enText: He was aware that he was wrong.
She is aware of the danger.

ex.chText: 她发现有个黑影在注视着她。
ex.enText: She was aware of a dark figure watching her.

synonyms.bx: 指意识到或知道某种情况存在的，也指通过感官觉察到某事物的，通常作表语，常后接介词 of 或 that 从句。

ex.chText: 他意识到他现在所做之事的重要性吗？
ex.enText: Is he conscious of the importance of what he is doing?

ex.chText: 我充分相信自己做的是对的。
ex.enText: I am fully conscious that I have done right.

ex.chText: 她无意识地把一只手放在他的手臂上。
ex.enText: Without conscious thought, she put a hand on his arm.

synonyms.bx: 指注意到或意识到某事物的，通常作表语，常后接介词 of 或 that 从句；也指思想、记忆等有意识的。

ex.enText: He was sensible of his guilt.

ex.chText: 她知道政治课不受欢迎。
ex.enText: She is sensible of the fact that politics is not a popular subject.

synonyms.bx: 指知道或意识到某事物存在或属实的，常后接介词 of。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：知道的，意识到的

tr: having awareness of surroundings and sensations and thoughts
example: became conscious that he was being followed
a conscious effort to speak more slowly

value.def: If you are conscious of something, you notice it or realize that it is happening.

example.ex: He was conscious of the faint, musky aroma of after-shave...
example.tran: 他注意到了须后水淡淡的麝香味。

example.ex: She was very conscious of Max studying her...
example.tran: 她非常清楚马克斯在仔细端详她。

example.ex: Conscious that he was becoming light-headed again, he went over to the window.
example.tran: 他意识到自己又开始头晕了，于是走向窗边。

gramarinfo.label: v-link ADJ <l>of</l> n/-ing, v-link ADJ that

value.def: If you are conscious of something, you think about it a lot, especially because you are unhappy about it or because you think it is important.

example.ex: I'm very conscious of my weight...
He is acutely conscious that this transition will bring with it the risk of social unrest.
example.tran: 他非常清楚这种转变伴随着社会动乱的危险。

gramarinfo.label: v-link ADJ <l>of</l> n/-ing, v-link ADJ that

value.tran: (尤指由于不满或自觉重要而)注意的，关注的

value.def: A conscious decision or action is made or done deliberately with you giving your full attention to it.

example.ex: I don't think we ever made a conscious decision to have a big family...
example.tran: 我觉得我们没有刻意地决定要生很多孩子。

example.ex: Make a conscious effort to relax your muscles.
Sophie was not consciously seeking a replacement after her father died.
example.tran: 父亲去世后，索菲并没有刻意地寻找替代他的人。

value.def: Someone who is conscious is awake rather than asleep or unconscious.

example.ex: She was fully conscious all the time and knew what was going on.
example.tran: 她一直都很清醒，知道是怎么回事。

value.def: Conscious memories or thoughts are ones that you are aware of.

example.ex: He had no conscious memory of his four-week stay in hospital...
example.tran: 他对自己住院的4个星期没有任何有意识的记忆。

example.ex: Beneath the conscious mind there are many levels of the unconscious.
example.tran: 在意识心理之下存在很多层次的无意识。

value.tran: (记忆或想法)有意识的，意识到的

example.ex: Most people cannot consciously remember much before the ages of 5 to 7 years...
example.tran: 大多数人在5至7岁之前没有多少有意识的记忆。

example.ex: Sometimes we are not consciously aware of these feelings.
example.tran: 有时候我们没有意识到这些情感。

trans: 意识到；意识到某事；认识到；意识到的

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + sci 知道 + ence 表行为 → 大家都知道，人要有良心 → 良心
con 共同 + sci 知道 + ous …的 → 都知道该怎么做 → 自觉的
ne 无 + sci 知道 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 无知的
omni 全部 + sci 知道 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 全知道的 → 无所不知的
pre 预先 + sci 知道 + ence 表行为 → 预先知道 → 先见之明
pre 前；预先 + sci 知道 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 有先见之明的
pseudo 假 + science 科学；学问 → 伪科学
sci 知道 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 知道，知识 → 学问
sci 知道 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 + ific 使…的 → 科学的
sub 下 + conscious 有意识的；自觉的 → 下意识的
